8: Welcome to Ambari Shell. For command and param completion press TAB, for assistance type 'hint'.

20: * blueprint add - Add a new blueprint with either --url or --file
21: * blueprint defaults - Adds the default blueprints to Ambari
22: * blueprint list - Lists all known blueprints
23: * blueprint show - Shows the blueprint by its id
24: * cluster assign - Assign host to host group
25: * cluster autoAssign - Automatically assigns hosts to different host groups base on the provided strategy
26: * cluster build - Starts to build a cluster
27: * cluster create - Create a cluster based on current blueprint and assigned hosts
29: * cluster preview - Shows the currently assigned hosts
30: * cluster reset - Clears the host - host group assignments
31: * configuration download - Downloads the desired configuration
32: * configuration modify - Modify the desired configuration
33: * configuration set - Sets the desired configuration
34: * configuration show - Prints the desired configuration
35: * debug off - Stops showing the URL of the API calls
36: * debug on - Shows the URL of the API calls
38: * hello - Prints a simple elephant to the console
41: * host components - Lists the components assigned to the selected host
42: * host focus - Sets the useHost to the specified host
43: * host list - Lists the available hosts
45: * script - Parses the specified resource file and executes its commands
46: * services components - Lists all services with their components
47: * services list - Lists the available services
48: * services start - Starts a service/all the services
49: * services stop - Stops a service/all the running services
